reviews: Great location, close to metro and a huge Park, close to many places to eat, staff is very helpful and friendly, breakfast is tasty and the room is cleaned daily. Next time I'm Paris I'll chose again this hotel. Thank You for a great experience!

We had a lovely stay in Hotel L'Interlude. The room was clean and well equipped. Breakfast was good and the staff very helpful and pleasant. Metro and bus stops just outside. Would definitely recommend.

Placed in a quite quiet neighborhood, this hotel has many advantages: 3 min walking to the nearest metro station, Michel Bizot, a lot of good places to eat in the near vicinity and many very useful mini markets for everyday needs. All the personnel of the hotel are very friendly and careful to the guests, trying to solve any problem. I will stay here again.

Adorable boutique hotel with very friendly staff, a cute lobby and beautifully decorated rooms and comfy beds. My room was on the smaller side but plenty big for one or two people. It looked out over the street, had a pretty French balcony, and was bright and airy. Delicious and generous complimentary breakfast is served in a cute room behind the lobby, and you can also eat or relax in the courtyard. The hotel's location is great if you are looking to be away from the busyness of the city centre. Lots of shops and restaurants, and walking distance to a huge park with a small lake, walking trails, woods, and the Parc Zoologique de Paris. A really relaxing spot if you want to relax and slow down a bit. Loved it; would definitely stay there again!

Very nice stay and a exellent service.
Good breakfast the people are working in the hotel very polite .
Nothing to complain we are coming for sure next time back to this hotel!
Everything was good to travel with the subway.

The room was on the last floor of the hotel. It was small, but nicely furnished. Everything was clean and the view was wonderful. Despite the (deliberate) street location, it was not too noisy. The staff were very friendly and accommodating. They spoke very good English, not a given in Paris.
Everything you need is nearby. The metro is very close to the hotel.
I will be happy to come back.

Interlude hotel is located in a very charming and quiet street of Paris. Although not Central, the Metro station of line 8 is only 2 steps away and you can be anywhere you want in about 30 minutes. The breakfast is tasty and served in a nice quiet and charming place. The staff was kind and hotel was clean with no problems whatsoever. You also have access to supermarkets, caffe, McDonalds, and a Tram station all in 1 minute walk distance. Getting to the hotel from both airports and vice versa is very easy. As someone who works in the Hotel and Tourism section i can safely say that Hotel Interlude is a very nice choise for your stay in Paris.

We had a rreally pleasant stay at Hotel d' Interlude. We stayed in a two-room chamber with 5 people. Service was excellent. They offered to put an extra bed in the double room, which was very attentive and kind. They also rang the parking for us to extend our parking.
Breakfast was all right, although sometimes you had to wait a little longer for the refill of the breads and pancakes. The breakfastroom was a bit small for all the guests, but we did not think that to be a problem. Beds were good and the room and bathrooms were clean. Towes were given every day and beds were made up as well.
Location is excellent since it is on a walking-distance from the metro. THe neighbourhood is quite charming and offers some nice and cosy reataurants.
All in all, we had the perfect stay at Hotel d' Interlude and we will sure come back to this hotel.

This hotel bucks the trend of the reputation a lot of hotels suffer from in Paris. The one negative it's location is a bit out of the city, travelling on the Metro is difficult as you have to transfer to other lines with no escalators or lifts, however the station is close to the hotel., Oh sorry one more, no fridge.
The rooms are compact but modern and clean with a great cleaning service daily. Air-conditioning works, and the bathroom is adequate.
The breakfast is a simple affair but the food is very high quality and plentiful. The breakfast person is a joy.
Actually all the staff are lovely, warm and welcoming especially dealing with my awful French. We were on the 6th floor with a fab view.
All in all this is great value for money, please give it a go..

small but nice rooms. Good hotel service for the room . in general the people in the hotel were very nice and friendly. Everything so far ok. We will come again if we are going to Paris.
Breakfast quality was good.

Hotel gave us the wrong room type (we booked superior they gave us classic). We had called to ask for an additional bed in the room for one night - which was confirmed and paid for upon arrival (where it was confirmed again!). Then, we left the hotel around 6pm - still no bed so I confirmed with the front desk who told us not to worry as the bed would be installed upon return. We came home at 1 am at night only to be informed that there was no third bed placed because the room was too small and that they gave us our money back for the extra bed. It’s 1 AM at that point - what were we supposed to do? The hotel literally did not give us any help whatsoever and the hotel manager is apparently unavailable if needed! One of us literally SLEPT ON THE FLOOR due to poor management!

Next morning went downstairs and was informed that there was a mixup because this extra bed is only available for a superior room - WHICH IS THE ROOM WE BOOKED!! Was then confirmed that we did not get a superior room and that the extra bed magically disappeared. HORRIBLE experience!

We wanted to get an obvious refund - and the hotel told us there was nothing they could do and to contact our booking operator. We - that same day - emailed them to ask them to formally confirm that our room was NOT a superior type and that we did NOT get the requested third bed. They are now reluctant to reply in any way whatsoever - which we already figured when leaving there , so we have a bunch of pictures and a recording where the reception clerk literally confirms all the above. I’m curious to see where this will go - and honestly happy to put my consumer policy into good use and put a lawyer on this. Hotel assistance is the absolute WORST we have EVER had. Good luck booking this hotel - especially getting something done if you have an issue, you are going to need it.

WOULD NOT RECOMMEND

dirty room, bad smelling, bathroom dirty, shower had mold. the breakfast plates were dirty as well. the advantage is very nice and helpful staff. unfortunately I won't visit this place anymore, waste of money. a pity because on booking.com it looked like a lovely and clean room.

Arrival: Night receptionist, Mussa, was courteous and efficient, although seemingly unaware that the wi-fi does NOT function in bedrooms, but only on the ground floor. (This poor availability is more appropriate to a hostel, rather than a 3* hotel ?)

The 2nd floor bedroom was relatively clean and tidy, but with some shortcomings. The hand towel was so frayed at the edges, and discoloured, it was clearly not of an appropriate standard. Both windows had greasy fingermarks, at eye level. And there was neither a bathrobe nor slippers, which were pre-requested.

I raised these points at reception, next morning.

Breakfast buffet: The regular provider was only around at the start of my stay. Her two replacements were not supervised, and it showed. No welcome or explanation to new diners; tables not cleared promptly after being vacated; and various items being unavailable due to depleted supply/stock, such as eggs, toasting bread and black tea. One even insisted on placing the toaster immediately beneath a basket container, clearly unaware of the potential fire risk.

On the first afternoon, after the room had been serviced, its two windows still had the greasy fingermarks. I reported this oversight to the receptionist, who personally came to the room, and cleaned the windows, herself - which I thought was an excellent response.

After that, I had no further complaints about the room, other than the permanent unavailability of wi-fi, and the television which was out of action for some 24 hours, awaiting repair. On the topic of TV, not all of the listed English-language channels were available - such as CNN and the two business ones - but at least BBC 1 & 2 were functioning.

The two "student vacation" receptionists were courteous and helpful throughout my stay, so a big thank you is due to both !

Overall, a comfortable and affordable hotel in a convenient and respectable area of Paris was let down by poor supervision, training and oversight.

P.S. Why are there no dessert spoons provided in the breakfast room ?

Good location hôtel. Clean service and breakfast team are great, as well as night shift receptionists.
The tourist experience could be better if the reception were aware of the neighborhood attractions, a tourist map and a metro map would be very much appreciated on arrival, but they had nothing.

Great location, close to Metro and the Bus, close to market's and Bistro's, very friendly and helpful staff, Breakfast was very good.
We done several daytrips to different locations we didn't get lost once.

This was our first time visiting Paris. We feel very fortunate to have found this great hotel at such a reasonable price (100 euros per night including breakfast for two).

This is a small hotel. Our room was accessed via a tiny lift and half a flight of stairs which was fine (we just had cabin bags). The room was big enough for two people with bags. The bed was very comfortable, and the bathroom was very nice. There is a jug and cups to make tea, but no fridge. Our room had a view from the second floor, and the double glazed windows and air-conditioning meant there wasn't any problem with street noise. Even though the hotel appears to be on a main road it was surprisingly quiet at night.

The staff at the hotel were friendly and helpful. Breakfast is simple but very nice, and again the service at breakfast was friendly.

The hotel is located in a quiet neighbourhood very close to a subway. Close to subway is critical we discovered, as this is the best way to get around Paris.

We would happily return here if we visit again.

Happy repeat customer here. After staying a number of times over the last 8 years, I appreciate how consistent the maintenance and services provided by the management and other staff members at this hotel. Professional, courteous, friendly and efficient, I have only praise for this establishment. Enjoyed the breakfast, appreciated the most recent changes in the menu. The room is very comfortable and well designed for my needs. Very clean. Great location for transit (subway, buses & streetcar). The neighborhood is worth exploring. The area is great for walking. Easy access from and to the CDG airport. I would certainly highly recommend.

Air conditioning, breakfast buffet. Big bed in a small room. Location between two subway stations of line 8, area not very touristy. Good shopping and a few restaurants, where many locals frequent.

Closet with doors would be ideal. Bathroom very small but in standard in Paris.

Extremely expensive (510 euros for 3 nights)
Room incredibly small
Dirty bathroom
failed wakeup call from the reception
I asked my room to be cleared by 1pm and they forgot to inform the cleaning team
They also tried to charge me a breakfast I never had

Staff were really nice. The place was a little more dated decor wise than expected but this didnt impact my stay.
Room was cleaned well. Breakfast was average. I preferred eating out.
The noise levels from my neighbours bothered me and my sleep. Constant door slamming, babies crying. TV super loud so it wasnt sound proof. You can hear them talking and slamming cupboard doors early morning/late. Jolted me awake more than once so that wasnt relaxing.
If you go out late you need to ring a bell to get back in. I had to wait a long time one night as reception was empty and kept ringing the bell. It was early hours.
The lift stopped working on my last day so i had to carry luggage down 6 flights of stairs.
Overall nice experience and if there were no other options i would go back. It does the job for a 3* budget when you stay/arrive.
Personally, i would spend more next time to stay a bit more up market for a full comfortable stay as a solo traveller.

Bathroom was not clean. Cleaning stuff think nobody understand serbian , so if you do understand you can listen abaut how guests are " manure , scum.... " When breakfast stuff changed there was no bread , no juice , no cheese , ......... . Location is ok couse metro is realy close to hotel.

We stayed at the Hotel L'interlude for 3 nights. The hotel was clean, comfortable and spacious. The staff were polite, helpful and friendly. Good location with many restaurants nearby. Would recommend this hotel to anyone.

Friendly and helpful staff, nice rooms, clean and neat. Good breakfast. The hotel is well located in the 12th, numerous cafes and bistros are near by. Easy access to the rest of Paris via the metro. Would stay here again.

Different room than we booked… not renovated, old.
No keys were available when we arrived so we got the master key, it’s was possible to open every hotel room with the master key! Totally unacceptable!

Good accomodation. Room wall a bit thin so that we heard rumors from other rooms.
Breakfast good. Would be better to add some fresh fruit.
Hotel position close to Metro station. Staff quite good. Room not so large but sufficient.

No refund, because of hotels policy. Could not stay there, because of covid.
Not very friendly management. Didn't like the payment policy, booking procedures. Not satisfied at all, bad experience, don't recommend.

It was a very nice stay at this well-located hotel. We were very satisfied, the staff was overall very friendly. The room and bathroom were clean. We were traveling with two kids and they liked it too.

My girlfriend and I stayed here for a night, and it was very nice. It's a pretty good hotel with very nice English speaking staff. We had the included breakfast and it was plentiful and delicious. I would come here again!

After arrival I had warm welcome by the Front office. The hotel has a good situation with Metro, Tram and Restaurants etc. nearby. Hotelroom was clean and has all you need.
The breakfast was good, again with very friendly staff just like the Reception.

Everything was perfect, the location it’s great, we only had to walk 3 minutes to take the subway and arrived everywhere we wanted to go, the attention was good, the room comfy and warm. Definitely if I come back to Paris I’ll stay there again.

located in the beautiful areas of the capital, we recommend visiting Paris during the holiday season because very beautiful light decorations in the streets, we were a little bored by the demonstrations but the hotel staff put us in safety by advising us the tourist sites to visit,
good size room and good breakfast

We spent 3 nights in this hotel and we are very enthousiastic. Friendly crew, clean rooms. Breakfast was great in a cost breakfast room.
Close to metrostation Bizot with nice restaurants in the direct neigbourhood.

I really recommend this hotel. First of all, the hygiene was so good. The room is cleaned every day. Personnel of the hotel was so helpful. They did what i wanted from them. So I again choose this hotel when I go back to Paris.

We are very happy to recommend the Hotel L'Interlude. Staff very friendly, rooms clean and well appointed. We found the help we received to locate points of interest around Paris was informative and the option of being so close to underground and bus services was a highlight

The sympathy of all the staff is incredible. The hotel is situated near a metro station so it’s easy to move across Paris. They offer coffee all day and some suits to eat around. I really recommend this place to stay.

Can’t recommend this hotel enough. The staff are so friendly and couldn’t do enough for us. The room was beautiful and very big. It was so clean and warm! The breakfasts are delicious and such a wide variety of choice. Thank you for a lovely stay. We will definitely be back.

Just returned from a lovely long weekend stay at this hotel. The staff are lovely, friendly and very welcoming. The hotel is in a great location and although away from the city centre it is only 30min metro trip away - which flies by! There is also a metro stop a stones throw away! Breakfast was fresh and perfect ahead of a day of exploring. Would recommend this hotel for a great city break stay.

The worst service was from Mary, she's the receptionist. Very impolite, doesn't help, makes bad faces on the phone talking to clients. Who can hire a person like this? I wrote a review in booking.
Benjamin is the only dedicated, kind, helpful person I've seen there. The man from the breakfast was ok.

My room was completely full of bed bugs, unfortunately, I noticed that during the day after my first night of sleep and I was able to kill 3-bed bugs that were super visible on my bed. I contacted the front desk during the night and the staff at that time tried to find the best solution possible, which consisted of a mattress on the floor (the hotel was fully booked and it was not possible to change rooms). During the morning I warned the front desk again and the answer that I got was: " I am sorry". All in all, it was the worse experience that I have ever lived in my travels, I would never recommend this place and will never go back. I also opened a formal complaint in the European Customers Services.

I needed a reasonably priced hotel for just one night in Paris, and this one fitted perfectly! Although the room was compact, it was beautifully clean, had a nice view across the street, and was conveniently located. If you are catching a bus from the Bercy bus station, then this hotel is well located. You can walk to the bus station, or it's a cheap taxi ride away. The staff were very polite and friendly, and helpful with any requirement. There is a choice of food options right on the doorstep, with nearby cafés, bakeries and supermarkets to choose from. I would go there again any time.

Overall a very nice experience staying in this hotel. Our room was spacious for a family of 4 (amazing bathroom), clean, modern. The location was great with an amazing Thai place, nothing flash but great food and also some amazing bakeries in the neighborhood, supermarket and 2 mins walk from Michel Bizot metro station.

I had heard Paris hotel were smaller in size compared to other European cities but nothing preosree me for this shocker ...it is so so so tiny that you have to put your suitcase on the bed each and every time you wanna open it.then there is zero space to put up stuff. Just a narrow ledge like cupboard plus the lift stops at a level between floors so you will be climbing up stairs with the suitcases.
Food..no eggs at breakfast which was a surprise.
Pros...very great location.next to the metro.bus stop.has lots of bakeries.eating places. Bathroom was obviously super small but has very good water supply and arrangements..has tea coffee maker .
Oh yes...the front desk staff is super helpful especially mohsin.
Net net a functional hotel .perfect for 2 nights .if a longer stay is planned may get claustrophobic.

Rooms were were clean bed was comfy staff were very friendly!
Easy and cheap to get into cetral paris (only 20mins).
They have baggage storage if you have a late flight out which is handy.
There are loads of lovely restuarants and bakerys close by and free wifi.

The hotel room, on the 6th floor was small, with a lovely view across the roof tops.
Although the room was tiny, the open windows made up for the small space. The room and the hotel was clean and quiet overall, a perfect location for business meetings in this area of Paris. It is located conveniently a few short steps from the Metro. Although the walls were rather thin, the neighbors were very understanding when I asked them to try to keep the noise down.

A lovely, traditional hotel in a very nice and quiet area. There are many bakeries, local shops and places to eat. There was a Sunday market which was nice to walk along. We went to two restaurants - Chez ma Belle Mere which is just across the road and Au Tramway - both had really lovely food. There is a park with a lake just up the road which is a peaceful place to walk. Perfect location for the Michel Bizot metro station - the hotel is about half an hour from the centre of Paris.

We had a small but comfortable room, on the top floor [there was a lift] with nice big window and view of the street. There was tea and coffee making facilities but no milk provided. Breakfast was great and just what we wanted - a lovely selection - pancakes were a added bonus! The reception staff were friendly and spoke good English.

A lovely hotel - we would definitely recommend.

small rooms but very clean and with all needed. a little bit too far from the centre. friendly and efficient staff. I would recommend to ask for a room on the backyard, front can be noisy because of the market in the morning.

We booked two nights here for a visit to Paris. The location is pretty good as there are shops, restaurants and a circus and zoo nearby. However, the circus was not open during the week in November as it is out of season.
It is close to Metro stations so very convenient.
The staff are friendly and speak English.
The lift is tiny, barely enough room for two people with cases, and you do have to climb stairs anyway as the lift stops between floors, however this was not really an issue for us.
The room was small but modern and clean. The bathroom was also small but adequate and clean.
My only complaint would be that there were no milk pots in the room and the tea and coffee were not replenished, however this is a minor issue and reception were happy to provide these when requested.
Breakfast was a standard continental breakfast and was nice enough.
You do have to pay city tax of around 1.70euros per person per night.
Overall a very good value hotel when visiting Paris, I would definitely return.

I love this hotel the staff are extremely friendly and nothing is too much trouble I’ve stayed here before and will stay again everything you need is on you door the bakery next door is amazing friendly and beautiful products the staff are great

We had an absolutely fantastic stay at the Linterlude hotel. The staff was super friendly, the hotel is quaint and located in the beautiful 12th arrondissement of Paris, away from all the tourists and hustle-bustle. The rooms were super clean, beds were very comfortable and everything was just about perfect. The complimentary breakfast is alright, although they don't serve eggs (which they really should).

Walk out at 7 in the morning and you'll smell freshly baked bread from a multitude of Boulangeries around, kids going to school, people jogging and bicycling. Take a 5 minute walk to the breathtakingly beautiful 'Lac Daumesnil' in the Park Bois De Vincennes (photos attached). This was most definitely the highlight of our stay here. We would go there every morning for a stroll and the 4km run around the lake was is beyond amazing.

There is a Fanprix supermarket just around the corner from where we'd get most of our daily shopping done. The Daumesnil metro station is a 7 minute walk which connects you to all of the major metro stations. The Eiffel tower is about a 25 minute ride (Mir Hakiem station). There are popular eateries like McDonalds and Subway just around the corner as well.

Highly recommended on your stay to Paris, especially if you want to stay away from the touristy bits and have an unadulterated Parisian experience!

Metro is 100mt from the hotel. So peaceful area. Rooms are so clean and staff is very polite. I really enjoy my trip. U can move easily to plaxe u wish to visit. I suggest this hotel to who want to visit tourist places in Paris

We stayed here for 3 nights whilst attending a concert. It is outside of the main city but in a really nice area with good transport links - Metro station and Tram a few minutes each way from hotel. Plenty of places to eat locally too, Villa Romana we particularly liked for the pizza, wouldn't rate much else we had some over cooked mussels, so just stick to the pizza its good !
The hotel itself was a good price, nice and clean with all the basic facilities you need. Corridors and hallways very old fashioned and in keeping with the building but the rooms, reception and small breakfast area were more modern. Bedrooms were small and bathrooms massive, but as we were visiting a city it was really just a clean bed and shower for the night. Breakfast was adequate, nothing special but you could get a drink and a few options of bread, pastries, yogurts, cheese, hams, jams etc
I you fancy a nice park, Parc de Bercy is just across the main road, lovely to walk around and get away from city life for an hour or two.

We booked 2 months in advance and were dismayed to get allocated an extremely tiny room on the 5th floor. I had stayed in that hotel a few years back, before the renovations so the room we stayed in has had a basic make-over, the beds were firm and the bathroom was basic and tiny but pleasant and clean. But the problem of that room was the size: there is hardly enough room for one bed but there were two twin beds! No room even for a luggage stand and we had to put our cases on the bed to get anything from them with our back touching the wall. It should be a single room not a double. When I mentioned this to the lady at the desk, she just said that it was like that in Paris and all the hotels in the area were the same because space is a premium. I know this, I was born in Paris! But then the price should reflect this and it definitely does not. The correspondence I consequently had with the manager revealed an arrogant attitude and a total lack of elementary courtesy towards a client. I will not recommend this hotel to any of my friends and I personally will not be back.

This was booked for my husbands birthday. Room clean breakfast room on the small side but adequate. Staff very helpful. Metro station nearby for sight seeing. All in all a very pleasant few days. Viva la France

Modern and clean hotel with friendly hotel staff! Metro just seconds down the road to get into the center of paris. Also had A few bakeries and brasseries located along the street if you don’t want to go far for food! I would stay here again!

I stayed here September 2018 for a week with my partner.

Positives:

- good value

- a comfortable bed and clean room

- excellent transport links (Michel Bizot metro stop is just down the road)

- continental breakfast was a bit lacking in choice but did set us up for the day, also the lady who ran the area was very nice and attentive (e.g. remembered us and that we have coffee)

Negatives:

- the room was supposed to be available at 2PM (check in time) however we had to wait 40 minutes for it to be cleaned first

- the room key had to be handed in every time we left the hotel, I thought this rule was a bit strange

Overall I would definitely recommend the hotel, in particular it was nice to be in a quieter area of Paris but still be able to travel easily. From the hotel it took approx. an hour to get to Disneyland Paris and under an hour for attractions such as The Louvre and the Eiffel Tower.

The Hotel is located right next to a metro station, so travelling the city is made very easy.The staff was very nice ans helped finding everything we wanted to see.The breakfast was alright, nothing special but enough to start The Day.Our room was small but really really nice!!

Clean, good looking and efficient, the room is a little small but it’s good for a couple and for a trip to Paris, located 2 minutes from the Michel Bizot station and so easy to reach every place of the city. The staff is absolutely kind and helpful, the breakfast it’s delicious and full of choices! I’m surely choosing this hotel again if I’m coming back to Paris. See you soon and thank you for the hospitality.

The hotel room is small, but really clean and comfortable. The bed is fantastic😊 the hotel is near to the metro 8 , so u can reach the Eiffel tower in 20 minutes. And the Nation Rer to go to Disneyland is near too.
It’s a good hotel for couples and families.
The staff was always gentle and all of them speak English😊

Me and my family stayed for four nights in Interlude Hotel in Paris. The hotel is very nice, clean and there is a metro station just 50 yard away, the area is very safe and there are some nice cafes, restaurants, bakeries, shops, Pharmacies and Supermarkets. The staff are very friendly the rooms are good with very comfy beds. The breakfast was good but there’s nearby bakery you can get your breakfast in. We booked two bedrooms and they put us one next each other with the street view. If we go again we will stay in it again. We are highly recommended the hotel.

The hotel was clean,staff was welcoming. Breakfast was the same every morning which was boring if you are on holiday and very less choice. I had to go and bring milk every time when making tea or coffee in the room even ironing board. Would prefer to go somewhere else next time.

We stayed for 3 nights. The staff was very friendly and the service was good. Dinner was delicious. The hotel is in a very relaxed place of Paris..not in a very busy environment and not very loud soundings in the night. Thats what we need. Thank you very much.

Nice hotel in a non-touristy part of Paris with convenient Metro connection. The room was clean and well maintained with a comfortable bed and quiet air conditioning. Staff were friendly, and helpful. The breakfast was very good - espresso coffee would have made it excellent.

Basic hotel with a basic breakfast. But perfect for a short city break away. Wall are thin so not the quietest but all guests seemed respectful. Very friendly hotel staff as well. Also in a great location from the Michel Bizot Metro stop and great water pressure in the showers

Stayed in this hotel for 2 nights. Landed in Paris airport and as first time travellers to Paris, dared to take a metro requiring 2-3 changes to Michel Bizot. Hotel is walkable from there (assuming you have luggage that can be easily dragged). Our room was facing the main road and although very compact room size, it was extremely clean and comfortable. Since we aimed to mostly be touring the city, we did not mind the small room. The breakfast was not very elaborate but had basic stuff. The show stealer were the croissants that were almost always freshly baked. Since this was a relatively smaller hotel, the breakfast was prepared as and when people kept coming. On a particular day, the croissants were over and the hotel staff kindly obliged to bake a round of fresh ones for us. The softest and best croissants I've ever had. Can go back just for that. If you do not mind travelling slightly more to reach the main destinations of Paris, you could try this hotel out.

Located one block from the Metro so easy to come and go. Excellent staff and friendly. Stayed for three nights and loved our beautiful little room with wonderful bath. Very comfortable. Would stay here again. Good breakfast.

I arrived late in the evening for my check-in and fortunately the bed was very confortable with very clean toilet and bath. The night staff was very helpful particularly when i needed to leave very early in the morning on my last day. The taxi he reserved for me and my daughter was very much on time.

A great place for a short stay . Handy transport links for the city sights plenty of places to eat and drink. Take a walk in the lovely Bois De Vincennes, maybe a row around the lake . Only a little gripe we had to ask for more coffee in the room as it was not replaced after use. all in all a good place for a short stay.

A very nice place to stay in, the breakfast is good, the reception staff is polite and helpful. The metro station is 4 min walking from the hotel. The rooms are clean and reformed, the only point to improve is maybe to put the small fridge in the room but nothing else.

We were on our second honeymoon in Paris last Sunday and stayed at this hotel with supposedly good reviews, We came back midnight on Monday from the Eiffel Tower after it rained heavily with muddy shoes. Hotel worker at front desk spoke little English so we used a toilet towel to clean our shoes as we didn’t want any mud to go on the carpets. The following day that wet dirty toilet towel was left on top of our white duvet with an angry letter from the manager demanding €10. We immediately spoke to the lady at the front desk who attempted to contact the manager who wasn’t available. We went outside for 5 minutes to the local convenience store and as we came back we found the female manager waiting for us looking visibly angry. As I attempted to explain what had happened she became angry, rude and passively aggressive at me and my wife stating that ‘we people in France don’t do this type of behaviour’, I didn’t know whether this was a racial/religious/nationalist attack on us, we are of Asian ethnicity. She would not entertain my explanation an told me multiple times to shut up. I apologise for gett8ng the towel dirty and agreed to pay a fee for the towel, she stated the small white toilet towel apparently costs €10 to purchase. I enquirer as to proof of this before I part with €10. She said she don’t have to show proof and she could’ve changed me €50 instead! I expla8ned to her where in the terms and conditions does it say she can start charging me for these things and of an inflated cost. When she realised she had nothing else to add to back her claims she rudely told me to shut up again, finish my stay that night and leave the next day. I was left gobsmacked, my wife visibly upset, that we had been rudely spoken to, abused, and wer both left mortified and fearing our own safety. I told the lady she had ruined our honeymoon, she said she didn’t care, told me to shut up, and leave the next morning. Her own receptionist looked startled as to the managers behvaiour. We had no option but to pay that excessive fee on our check out. We would like to say we are both working professionals with good jobs, we have stayed in Dubai for 10 nights in our first part of our honeymoon, and we have stayed in multiple hotels in the UK and across the world prior to getting married, and never have we experienced such shocking, poor, rude, aggressive customer service, let alone from the hotel manager! DO NOT BOOK WITH THIS HOTEL, AVOID AT ALL COST!!!

The hotel has good metro connection to the city center. Rooms are small but modern, stylish and clean. Service is exceptional, the breakfast/Kitchen team is quick and works flawless in the background. Speaking of breakfast: its not the big buffet you would expect on a pricey high standard hotel, but its good value for the money. Otherwise you could go to a bakery or cafe nearby. On our arrival the lift was not working, that was a bit of a bummer, because getting the luggage onto 4 floor after a 40 minute walk from quai de bercy was not so nice. But the lift was repaired next day, so no worries about that. Wifi was ok, but not the fastest. Biggest concern for us were other guests. An italian family with wild children can be enervating, when the come home loudly after eleven at night. But thats not the staffs problem, thats just a question of good behaviour. The staff was always very friendly a helpful. You can use a computer to print E-tickets in the lobby.

Nice hotel, calm and very clean, modern rooms, silent elevator. Excellent service.
Only the breakfast room is much too small, very narrow and noisy and the service unable to cope with the amount of guests. Displeasing start for the day.

Just two nights in Paris, but lovely stay at Hotel Interlude. Second time there - very convenient for us. Room is clean and comfortable. Staff are extremely happy and the breakfasts are superb. Will definitely book again

This hotel is an lovely location and a great place to get into the centre of Paris.The hotel is spotless and the rooms although cosy came with all you need all the staff are lovely and greet you warmly with a smile 😊 plus are helpful with the map locations didn’t want to leave Paris or the hotel great full on weekend thank you

The room was really nice if you booked the room for 4. The rest of the rooms are small. Street had some food, and nice locals tho few knew english. We stayed 4 nights and didnt get roomservice once. Tried to get them to change bedsheets, but they couldn't so we slept in blankets.

Very pleasant and comfortable stay at the lodge. the location, despite the location in comparison with the rest of the districts of Paris, is well located towards the metro stations Michel Bizot (300ft) and Porte Dorée (700ft), besides, there are a couple of supermarkets (Franprix and Monoprix) around, and some fruit shops and boulangeries at less than 500ft away. Clean rooms and the breakfast is well served.

This hotel is located in the 12th District which is not closed to the touristic attractions but is instead located in the middle of a nice suburban area. The subway is a few steps from the hotel main entrance and as a result, it gives you the opportunity to leave early in the morning and come back late after a whole day in the city. The farmer market on Sundays was a nice and unexpected surprise. Good hotel for business and vacations, as well as families and couples! Thank you L’interlude for a fantastic Parisian experience.

This was our second visit in Paris. The hotel is fantastic, especially for this price. The area is very nice, next to the Metro station Michel Bizot, Park Bois de Vincennes and super markets. Easy zone without suspicious dark faces !!! Clean room with WIFI, TV with 60 international programs, free tea and coffe, nice new fornitures. Good breakfast, good hours. Very nice STAFF, Thanks !!! Next to hotel there are a lot of restaurants with all type meal and prices, under is a great roast meat and chicken place good price, up the corner there is Burger King and Mcdonalds too. A good place to stay.

Metro right next to it, 20-25 min ride into town center. Nice, small hotel. Rooms quite small but clean and breakfast is basic but everything you need. Price good for what you get and for an hotel in paris....

Me and my wife had a two night stay at the Hotel L’interlude Paris. The hotels very easy to get too on the metro with the Michel Bizot station on route 8 a short walk away.
We read other reviews and read that there was not a lot around we found the opposite, the restaurant opposite the hotel s well worth a visit and walking up the main road Avenue Doumesnil there are many places to eat and drink all in all we had a great stay the rooms are a bit cosy but the showers are very powerful and the rooms are immaculately clean. You are on the main road but you get the sense of Parisian life.

Cheap but nevertheless comfortable. Rooms are small and modern with all the facilities you would need. I liked the area: lac Daumesnil, promenade plantee and the jardin de Reuilly are great places for running/ walking. Next to the metro stop, access is easy into the city centre or even to Disneyland and plenty of interesting restaurants in the neighbourhood.
Staff at reception were friendly and helpful 24/7; looked after our luggage for the whole day after checking out and even let us check in early on our arrival.
Overall, good quality for your money although, like in all hotels, the breakfast is too expensive. Better to go to the local boulangerie and fill your boots.

Very friendly and clean hotel near two metro stations (Michel Bizot and Daumesnil).
The room were we stayed was clear and big.Also the bathroom was fully equipped. I must say that the Staff were helpful and polite.

We stayed for 4 nights with breakfast included which by the way was delicious.

There are plenty of restaurants near the hotel and there is also a bakery next door which is excellent.

HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!

Sitting in the lobby as I write this. It has been almost 45 minutes that we have been waiting. The check in was 2.30 PM. We arrived after a long flight, tired and waiting to hit the bed and take some rest.

The receptionist informed that the room isn't ready. Inspite of the fact that we reached an hour after the actual check in time.
Very very disappointed with the service. Such a let down. All the good reviews about this hotel don't seem to make sense to me now. Already regret having booked this property for three days, all the more because I am traveling with my parents and it is their first trip here.

Hugely NOT RECOMMENDED! They've already spoiled the beginning of our trip! Such a spoiler.

We went to Paris with some friends for a long weekend (4 nights) and found this small hotel very close to the Convention center we were attending. The room was a little smallish but did perfectly well for us as we did not spend a lot of time there. The bathroom was very clean and the personnel of the hotel was very friendly and helpful all the time. I

t's really well situated with a Metro station nearby and plenty of places around to eat (Italian Pizzeria, fastfood, Thai...) or take a drink at nights in the bar just in front.

Having a bakery just next to it is a perfect fit when you can taste local products everyday there! Also, there is a supermarket very close to it so you can buy supplies for the day when going for tourism.

If I go back to Paris, I would definitely try this hotel again!

The room was small but clean and had everything we needed. Shower was brilliant! The hotel is situated literally less than 100 meters from Michel Bizot Metro stop-you can be in central Paris is no time.
On Sunday morning there is an extensive market on the street outside the hotel.
When we stayed, the hotel was quite and we slept well.
The breakfast was Continental-coffee, fresh juice and croissants suited me perfectly.
The hotel is a short was from a large beautiful park and also Paris Zoo (well worth a visit).
We used the luggage store room free of charge, and the wifi was free too.
The staff were so friendly and accommodating (man with moustache whose name I didn't catch-thank you for being so helpful and welcoming!). I'd highly recommend this hotel as a safe bet and convenient place to stay.

Clean, Friendly and accommodating staff, nice rooms although small yet this seems to be the norm for Paris. The hotel is close to food and trains (Metro). Our room was to the rear of the hotel so our view was of roof tops, buildings and the beautiful sky.

The rooms are clean, quiet and comfortable.
A lot of restaurants and shops in the neighborhood
The hotel is at one minute from the underground station Michel bizot.
However you cannot take away the keys of your room when you go out. You have to leave them to the staff. That's not very convenient.

We stayed here for 3 nights. Everything about this hotel was perfect. Great location, less than a 5 minute walk from the Metro and with lots of shops & restaurants nearby. The staff were very friendly & welcoming. The room was ideal, with daily cleaning and fresh towels. We asked for extra pillows on our second day and came back that evening to find they'd been provided. Will definitely come back for another stay.

I went to this hotel recently and had a thourghly good time. Their is a usual amount of space for a capital city hotel. It cookes a nice continental breakfast which ranges from crossiants to yohgurts to crepes. It might cost a little bit more than eating out. It is based in a nice residential area which is around nice local restaurants. It is a few stops away from the centre in michael bizot. The main line is 8 on the metro which isnt a mager line but has a few stops linking to line 1.

My 13 year old son and I have just stayed here for 3 nights. The rooms are the size you would expect for Paris. They were clean and tidy. The beds were comfortable. We asked for an extra pillow each and reception sorted it straight away. Very polite and friendly staff. The breakfast, although quite expensive was nice enough and you could help yourself to as much as you like. All a good standard.

The only negative is the noise from the road if you overlook Avenue Damuesnil. It's noisy at all times of the day.

The location although away from the city centre, the metro is only a few minutes walk away. The neighbourhood was nice and mainly with locals going about.

I would return.

Very nice, cosy and clean hotel. Good location, short walk to metro. Staff was very nice, one even taught me french! Our room was a bit small, but no too small. Everything worked well! Breakfast was pretty basic but did the job.I would go again and also recommend for others! :)

My partner and I stayed at this hotel for 2 nights and just about 3 days. We found the hotel on quite a busy street with a lot going on outside so was noisy. I didn't like the fact we couldn't turn the aircon on (I know it's February but it was really stuffy with the heating and everything on) we couldn't keep the window open over night as they would just open the whole way. Would've been better to have a latch on the window to allow air into the room. The rooms are really small but didn't expect anything big for a 2 night stay. The lift was a bit unsafe (if staying on floor 3 make sure you are careful on the stairs as you get out of the lift). I also didn't like the fact we had to leave the room key every time we left. Our room was clean and tidy. I would definitely recommend a mini fridge in the room as we had to buy drinks instead of having them charged on our room bill. The shower was lovely. The man behind reception was very helpful - I didn't rate the breakfast at all. For €11 it was over priced. Some staff made us feel quite uncomfortable and kept lingering around us. Overall we wouldn't go back to Paris, but we think the hotel is 5/10. We drove to Paris and the car park wasn't very safe. We felt extremely uncomfortable and wouldn't go back.

We got this hotel wrapped up with Eurostar tickets from London. Shared a twin room, clean, generous bathroom, great deal.The room overlooked Ave.Daumesnil, an interesting street, with metro a very short walking distance. We were doing sight seeing and visiting friends - (try the Rush Bar, Rue St Sebastian), so we found it very convenient to travel around the city. Food at le 217 was good, avoid the Italian at the top end near the park.
Staff were lovely and helpful, breakfast good and staff attentive. I'd go back, excellent value.
I was pleased with the lift, as we were on the top floor, but be careful if alcohol has been consumed as the lift comes out half way between floors with no landing! Plenty of character!

We stayed for 3nights, the room eas perfect and also the location is perfect to move to the center of the city, metro station is only 100meters after.
The staff was very helpfull and very gently specially the night manager.
We hope to visit Paris again.

My wife and I just returned from a 3 night stay at Hotel L'interlude, staying between Christmas and New Year. The rooms are small but on a par was almost all central Paris hotel rooms. The hotel itself is modern and well kept. Importantly, the location of the hotel is very convenient due to its proximity to a metro station which made exploring Paris much easier.

The hotel offers a pleasant continental breakfast buffet which has a nice variety of pastries, bread, cereal and fruit.

Our hotel room was clean without being sparkling and although the road outside can be noisy the windows on the rooms massively reduces this to the point that you could only hear the traffic if the window was open.

The staff were all very pleasant and welcoming.

Overall I would highly recommend a stay at the Hotel L'Interlude as I doubt you would find many budget hotels better.

I am puzzled to see that some people granted 4 points to this very basic, uncomfortable hotel, located on a noisy street (some of the rooms) and is way too expensive for what it is...
The elevator stops between the floors, so if you have heavy luggage you'll have to carry it up or down the stairs anyways... the rooms are small and very basic, and you can hear everything that's going on in your neighbors' rooms (TV, people taking, baby screaming, people walking....)
The rooms are quite clean but not sparking clean.

It is really a good hotel with easy access to metro. However it is not in centre of Paris (for Eiffel Tower it took us 30 mins travel from the hotel). I didn't worry too much about the location of the hotel as this is my first Paris visit so travelling is part of the trip to explore Paris.

Hotel staff were really helpful and speak english(most of them). I stayed in the ground floor room which is located next to smoking zone and laundry room. So a bit noisy in the night.

I travelled to the hotel from CDG by taxi as this was my first time in Paris and don't want to explore the train lines in night with young children. But while coming back realised it would cost atleast half the money if using metro and 30 minutes more, so took the taxi again arranged by hotel in 10 minutes.

Overall a very good experience and would recommend for family.

Thanks
Kes

We choose this hotel as it shows on their official website that they have an elevator. But we got the room that have to use the stairs!!!!!Our groups have to bring our big baggage to the room by ourselves without any help from the hotel staff.

When we arrived the hotel we also have a problems during check-in they cannot find our booking although we show them the voucher they still confirmed us that they did not see our booking so we have to contact our travel agents again to solve the problems and travel agent said that the hotel misunderstanding for the booking. It make us wasting time almost 1 hour

For the second night there is 1 room in our group power outage so we have to ask them to fix it.

Overall it's terrible experience for our group for this hotel. Please avoid it if you have other choice.

The hotel was very pleasing. We were welcomed on arrival and were happy with the room. ( which was small but comfortable. ) The breakfast buffet and the coffee was good. The hotel is within 2 mins. of the Michel Bizot Metro station platform ,( on the number 8 line towards Creteil. ) There are shops right beside the hotel but our room overlooking the street on the 4th. floor was quiet. The price we paid was very good value at less than 150 Euros for three nights bed and breakfast for the two of us ( plus the city tourist tax of 1.65 Euros per person per night).

While the hotel is quite basic in what it provides, it was perfect for us on our first trip to Paris. Got a double room for a great price on one of the price compare sites, located right beside a metro station it was very convenient for access anywhere in the city. It's situated on a beautiful avenue with nice restaurants and bakeries very close by. The service was fantastic, with staff more than happy to help us with whatever we needed. The room was small like most Paris rooms but it was very clean and comfortable with a lovely view out onto the street. We would 100% happily stay here again on future trips.

The hotel is about 10 mins from the centre on line 8 of the metro -station: Michel Bizot. It is in a lively residential area and close to; cafe /bars, bakeries a pizza place, local supermarkets, Chinese and Japanese takeaways. Also a short stroll away is the elevated park. The staff were friendly and there was a good range of guide books to borrow in the lobby area. the room was a little small but perfectly formed, we were at the front looking onto the main road, the windows were double glazed so noise not too much of an issue. Only downside was no in-room safe.
